param.value: Constipation is something that everyone has likely experienced at one time or another. But for some people, constipation can be more than just an occasional event. These people may experience irritable bowel syndrome with constipation (IBS-C) or chronic idiopathic constipation (CIC).
Trulance can help you find relief from the symptoms of your constipation
Trulance helped people with IBS-C have LESS stomach pain and bloating during bowel movements
Simple dosing makes once-daily Trulance easy to take.
Uroguanylin works best in the small intestine, where—based on the changing pH levels—it provides the right amount of fluid to create well-formed stool*
REDUCE STOMACH PAIN AND INCREASE FREQUENCY
It may seem like you’re the only one who is dealing with irritable bowel syndrome with constipation (IBS-C) or chronic idiopathic constipation (CIC), but there are millions of people just like you.
Trulance is the first medication for IBS-C and CIC that is designed to work like a natural peptide in your body.

Trulance is the first medication for irritable bowel syndrome with constipation (IBS-C) and chronic idiopathic constipation (CIC) that’s designed to work like a natural peptide in your body called uroguanylin (pronounced “yur-oh-gwah-nih-lin”). To best understand how uroguanylin works, let’s take a closer look at what happens in your body during the process of digestion.

Tell your doctor if you experience any side effects while taking Trulance. In clinical studies, 4.3% of people with irritable bowel syndrome with constipation (IBS-C) and 5% of people with chronic idiopathic constipation (CIC) taking Trulance experienced diarrhea versus 1% in placebo (sugar pill) group.
Irritable Bowel Syndrome with Constipation, or IBS-C, is a condition where one experiences long periods of constipation accompanied by stomach pain and bloating.
Uroguanylin has also been shown to reduce stomach pain* *This activity was seen in animal studies. The relevance to humans is not yet known.

Talking to your doctor is an important first step to managing your IBS-C or CIC. Asking the right questions about constipation can help you and your doctor get closer to finding a treatment plan that works for you. Getting ready for that conversation is as easy as 1-2-3.
Trulance is a prescription medicine used in adults to treat IBS-C or CIC. It can help provide more regular, well-formed bowel movements with less IBS-C related stomach pain and bloating.*
Identify your treatment goals with the Bristol Stool Form Scale
The Bristol Stool Form Scale is a visual representation of the 7 different types of bowel movements that you can have.
Type 4 is considered a well-formed bowel movement—described as smooth, soft, sausage- or snake-shaped, and free of lumps or excess liquid
Type 1 or 2 is often considered constipation, while Type 6 or 7 is often considered diarrhea
Trulance can help people have “normal” (smooth, soft, sausage- or snake-shaped) bowel movements
In addition to symptoms of CIC, patients with IBS-C also have stomach pain.
Trulance can help you have MORE regular, well-formed bowel movements with less stomach pain and bloating*,†

Managing Irritable Bowel Syndrome with Constipation (IBS-C) or Chronic Idiopathic Constipation (CIC) can be a challenge. But whether you’ve just been diagnosed with IBS-C or CIC, or have been dealing with it for a while, one thing is for sure—when managing constipation, your goal should be More regular, well formed bowel movements with less IBS-C related stomach pain and bloating*.
